Sasarin belched a burst of flame, igniting a small patch of forest and then circling above it, observing for an opportune moment. Curiously, as he slowed down, the strange high-pitched screams coming from behind him also ceased. Sasarin forgot that there was still a passenger on his back.
"Please, Tenuk, you haven't always remained a human before, have you!"
"Flying by yourself and suddenly being dragged away by a huge pink dragon are two different things!"
"Still okay, Kayer?"
Kaiye clearly disagreed with Nixi's statement, looking paler than usual as his claws were deeply embedded in Sasilin's back, drawing blood from the Slaques. Nevertheless, Sasilin seemed indifferent. Still, Sasilin realized he had frightened his new friend and decided to land on an open space.
"Sorry sorry, I detected an odor. I need to take care of it!"
"Do you have to drag us along too?" Tenuk climbed down from Sarsarin's back and slid to the ground along its tail, asking with a sharp tone. "We left Retvik behind! We abandoned that strong, brawny giant! How will he find us?"
"He will find a way..." Ni Xi said with approval. "Revtvik may be slow-witted, but he's not stupid."
"Can Reutvik drive?"
Nisi blinked and turned to look at Tenuk. "Of course he knows how to drive."
Have you ever seen Latvik drive? He doesn't have a truck like yours, and I've never seen him drive a cute little car like Kayle's. He only started riding in a car to work because you always drove us. He only has one bicycle.
A burst of laughter interrupted them. Sasilin suddenly couldn't stop laughing, but no one knew what he found amusing. It took Sasilin a while to calm down.
"Sorry sorry, just now I imagined this big guy clad in armor as your friend, riding a children's bicycle specially designed for Themosen kids. That image was too silly! I wish I had telepathy. This idea is too interesting! I must treasure it!"   Note: There seems to be a name that doesn't have a clear translation context, "Themosen", which appears to be a brand or a place name. It would be best to keep it as is unless you have more information about its origin and how it should be translated.
Kayel also smiled because he could imagine what Sasilin was thinking. "Alright, alright. But what did you smell? Why fly so fast?"
Sasarin snorted and took off, disappearing quickly before flying back and leaving a corpse in front of Nixie. It was an Orozarak, a very rare golden-white dragon-like creature. But its head was missing. "Another one dead. I heard their cries, smelled their blood. I must protect them and hunt the killer. This is Isini's will. Those creatures are nearby."
The powerful Slacker suddenly stiffened. Nix and Kayel also froze, their attention drawn to a gap at the edge of the clearing. A massive and black entity was staring at them, hissing. It then suddenly spread its two pairs of immense wings and charged forward, its target锁定萨萨林，完全不顾挡在其与萨萨林之间那三个小家伙。Kayel and Tenuk barely managed to sidestep, but Nix found herself being dragged down and nearly thrown into Sazalin's body.
Sasalin grabbed onto Nisi with one hand and tossed her onto its back using its long and dexterous tail, then leaped into the air. The black creature with two pairs of wings quickly followed.
Kayer made a disapproving noise and drew his rifle from behind. He then opened the bag and took out a magazine of ammunition. He hung the magazine in front of him for easy access, but soon realized that both Nishi, Salsalin, and the monster were nowhere to be seen.
"Hey, Tenuk, can you transform into a flying animal?" Kayer asked.
"Do you want to go after them?"
"Blabber." or "Nonsense."
"But... one of them is a giant monster!"
"So what? This rifle in my hands is powerful and can fire at any time. I just need to see it, and I can bring it down."
Tentok hesitated for a moment before taking a step back, giving himself some space. With a low, slightly painful groan, Tentok's body stretched out, his fur transforming into scales, and his arms turning into wings. He quickly shifted into an ordinary light blue Slaad, but his eyes remained red.
"Come up."
Tentuk now appears to be an ordinary Slacker, with neatly arranged scales growing on his back and a pair of spines that Caiyer can grasp. It took Tentuk a long time to take off, but once he was airborne, he quickly adjusted his direction and began to chase vigorously.
However, Tenuk and Kayer soon realized they weren't facing just one opponent. A second dark monster darted out from beneath them, and Tenuk barely avoided a collision.
"I guess this is the terrifying big monster that Laneous was worried about," Cayel furrowed his brow as he tried to shoot the second monster but missed, and quickly reloaded.
Tenuk did not respond; he was busy flying towards Nyx and Sarsen, despite the monster chasing them. Cayel clumsily turned around to face the monster. Cayel thought this was good news because it would be easier to aim and shoot. Two bullets tore through the monster’s upper wing, causing it to howl in pain as it disappeared into the trees. Cayel was uncertain if it was still following them, but he felt confident that it wouldn’t be able to keep up.
In front of them, Sasa林 was wildly swinging its body and spraying fire at the black monster. Nixi, meanwhile, was desperately clinging to Sasa林 to avoid falling off. Although the monster certainly appeared injured, it seemed to be furious and unwilling to back down. Moreover, the fireballs didn't seem to have caused much damage. After steadying itself, Nixi took the opportunity to pull out her weapon—a shotgun she trusted implicitly. Of course, a shotgun wouldn't be effective against such a monster, but perhaps the scattered bullets could scare off this black beast?
